   PAKISTAN-RDP (Islamabad, Pakistan) _ Pakistan's military ruler,
saying his nation had ``hit rock bottom,'' redrew its government
Sunday night, creating a military and civilian council to run the
country and giving no timetable for relinquishing the absolute
power he seized five days ago. By Tim Weiner and Steve LeVine.
