<HEADLINE>
HOCKEY'S NET EFFECT GOES TO EXTREMES
</HEADLINE>
 (For use by NYTimes News Service clients) 
By TOM HOFFARTH  
 c.1999 Los Angeles Daily News  
 
<TEXT>
<P>
   &LR; The goal of Buffalo Sabres fan Jeffrey Spring is that no one
forgets the goal that ended last season's Stanley Cup finals.
</P>
<P>
   With a Web site and resisting an NHL cease-and-desist letter,
Spring has sprung into action.
</P>
<P>
   The league office was upset that the site (www.nogoal.com) had
photos of the controversial goal that Dallas' Brett Hull, with his
skate in the crease, put past Buffalo's Dominik Hasek in
double-overtime last June.
</P>
<P>
   After consulting a lawyer, Spring took the pictures down, even
though he reasons they were shown all over the world. He does,
however, continue to sell shirts and caps with the site's logo _ a
Cup with the red circle and slash through it _ and present his
manifesto as to why this injustice should be thrown in the league's
face at every opportunity.
</P>
<P>
   __ Taking to another level the idea that hockey is a religion,
there's a Kentucky-based site (www.hockeyrosary.com) that, as the
URL implies, offers a unique puck-prayer bead string.
</P>
<P>
   For those moments of despair, the Cusick Creations' trinket
(selling for $20) uses the standard Catholic rosary-bead idea,
leading down to a miniature Stanley Cup charm. And it's available
in all team colors.
</P>
<P>
   __ NFL bylaws limit the ownership group of a team to 25 _ this
came after the Green Bay Packers' stock-option plan _ but that
restriction might be challenged by a group of New York Jets fans
who have been trying to rally support at a site
(www.buythejets.com) to have a bunch of people ante up just a
little and purchase the franchise that's currently seeking
ownership.
</P>
<P>
   The NFL could open itself to antitrust violations if it refuses
the eventual bid. It's worth keeping an eye on how this progresses.
</P>
<P>
   __ Sony Online Entertainment has launched a game called ``Sports
Jeopardy!'' on its site (www.station.sony.com) as well as a special
set-up site (www.sportsjeopardy.com).
</P>
<P>
   __ The new University of North Carolina basketball uniforms,
which were designed by Michael Jordan's new company called Jordan
Brand, have been previewed on the school's Web site
(www.goheels.com). According to the Charlotte Observer, the local
response has been overwhelming distain toward the design.
</P>
<P>
   __ Next year, another pro spring-football league wants to get
six to 10 teams to play a 12-week schedule that has a championship
game played on Memorial Day. For an update on its progress, it has
a site (www.springfootball.com). &QL;
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
