<SLUG> BC-SPACEHOTEL-RESORTS-SFCHRON </SLUG>
  
 THEY'LL LEAVE THE STARLIGHT ON FOR YOU  &HT;     By TERRY NAGEL 
 &HT;     c.1999 San Francisco Chronicle 
<TEXT>
<P>
   SAN FRANCISCO _ Some people believe that the key to creating
interest in space travel is offering travelers a destination rather
than just a suborbital flight.
</P>
<P>
   The Space Island Group of West Covina, Calif., says it could
build a large space resort within seven years. It would keep the
cost down by using ``space junk'' _ external fuel tanks discarded
by space shuttles. Sketches of its wheellike design look like
something out of the movie ``2001.''
</P>
<P>
   Robert Bigelow envisions building space hotels in about 15
years. He's the owner and president of Budget Suites of America and
Bigelow Aerospace, both in Las Vegas. His space company already has
hired teams to evaluate different hotel designs. As a first step,
Bigelow said the company would build an orbiting industrial park &LR; 
to serve companies working in space &LR; .
</P>
<P>
   Richard Branson of Virgin Atlantic Airways in England has
announced his intention to design a Virgin Hotel that would be
reached via a new airline called Virgin Galactic Airways. &LR;  Branson
already has registered the airline.
</P>
<P>
   &LR;  Brian Hustig hopes that NASA will stay out of the
hotel-designing business. He's a senior designer with an
architectural firm that designs space resorts: Wimberly Allison
Tong &AMP; Co. of Newport Beach, Calif. ``People from NASA are coming
from a military background,'' he said. ``The last thing you want is
to have the U.S. government design the place where you spend your
vacation.''
</P>
<P>
   Hustig thinks that people will need more than zero-gravity to
keep them amused in space. He imagines space visitors playing
unique games while floating weightless (``Nerf soccer or
something'') and attending themed parties. ``The whole station
could be designed like `Star Wars,' and you could go up there and
become an alien for an evening,'' Hustig said.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
<TRAILER>
NYT-10-17-99 2316EDT &QL; 
</TRAILER>
</DOC>
